PRISON BREAK
Architecture & Repository Layout

2D Real-Time Multiplayer Game (Go + Ebiten)

1. High-Level Architecture
Core Principles

Server authoritative simulation

Clients send inputs only

Fixed tick rate simulation

Deterministic game core

Shared game model between client and server

Thin client, thick server

Mobile + Desktop support via Ebiten

Stateless gateway layer (optional for scale)

Runtime Architecture
Clients (Mobile/Desktop)
    |
    |  WebSocket (JSON or Protobuf)
    v
Game Server (Go)
    |
    |  Authoritative Simulation Loop (fixed tick)
    |
State Broadcast (delta snapshots)
Simulation Model

Server runs fixed timestep loop (e.g. 30 or 60 ticks/sec)

Each tick:

Consume queued player inputs

Apply to deterministic world state

Resolve combat, abilities, timers

Evaluate win conditions

Emit state delta

Clients:

Send input commands with timestamp

Receive authoritative snapshots

Interpolate between snapshots

Never simulate authority-only logic

