4. Simulation Loop (Server)

Pseudo:

for range ticker.C {
    inputs := inputBuffer.Consume()
    game.ApplyInputs(inputs)
    game.Update()
    snapshot := game.GenerateDelta()
    broadcaster.Broadcast(snapshot)
}

Single-threaded simulation loop.
Networking runs in separate goroutines.
All world mutation happens inside game loop thread.

No race conditions allowed.

5. Networking Model
Transport

Start with:

WebSockets

Binary encoding (Protobuf preferred later)

UDP not required for 5–12 players.

Snapshot Strategy

Full snapshot on join

Delta snapshots per tick

Send only changed entities

Include server tick ID

Client interpolates between last 2 snapshots.

6. Mobile Considerations

Abstract input layer

Joystick component

Avoid overdraw

Sprite atlas batching

Fixed timestep independent of render framerate

Lock simulation at 30 ticks on mobile

7. Scaling Strategy

For 5–12 players per match:

One goroutine per match

Horizontal scale by spawning match instances

Stateless matchmaker

Redis optional for lobby tracking

